## Direct Dependencies

  blake3 v1.8.3
    Authors: Jack O'Connor, Samuel Neves
    License: CC0-1.0 OR Apache-2.0 OR Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
    https://github.com/BLAKE3-team/BLAKE3
    Use: BLAKE3 hash function for deterministic token identity (i32 ID).
         Every TokenVector.id is a truncated BLAKE3 hash.

  aes-gcm v0.10.3
    Authors: RustCrypto Developers
    License: Apache-2.0 OR MIT
    https://github.com/RustCrypto/AEADs
    Use: AES-256-GCM symmetric encryption for the vector database.
         FIPS 197 + SP 800-38D compliance.

  ml-kem v0.3.0-rc.0
    Authors: RustCrypto Developers
    License: Apache-2.0 OR MIT
    https://github.com/RustCrypto/KEMs
    Use: ML-KEM-1024 post-quantum key encapsulation (FIPS 203).

  ml-dsa v0.1.0-rc.7
    Authors: RustCrypto Developers
    License: Apache-2.0 OR MIT
    https://github.com/RustCrypto/signatures
    Use: ML-DSA-65 post-quantum digital signatures (FIPS 204).
         Tamper detection for encrypted database files.

  serde v1.0.228
    Authors: Erick Tryzelaar, David Tolnay
    License: MIT OR Apache-2.0
    https://github.com/serde-rs/serde
    Use: Serialization framework for database binary format.

  bincode v1.3.3
    Authors: Ty Overby, Francesco Mazzoli, David Tolnay, Zoey Riordan
    License: MIT
    https://github.com/servo/bincode
    Use: Binary serialization codec for vector database entries.

  clap v4.5.60
    Authors: The clap contributors
    License: MIT OR Apache-2.0
    https://github.com/clap-rs/clap
    Use: Command-line argument parsing for the morphlex/JStar CLI.

  memmap2 v0.9.10
    Authors: Dan Burkert, Yevhenii Reizner, The Contributors
    License: MIT OR Apache-2.0
    https://github.com/RazrFalcon/memmap2-rs
    Use: Memory-mapped file I/O for database access.

  rand v0.8.5
    Authors: The Rand Project Developers, The Rust Project Developers
    License: MIT OR Apache-2.0
    https://github.com/rust-random/rand
    Use: Random number generation for cryptographic nonces.

  getrandom v0.2.17 / v0.4.2
    Authors: The Rand Project Developers
    License: MIT OR Apache-2.0
    https://github.com/rust-random/getrandom
    Use: OS-level entropy source for cryptographic operations.

  thiserror v1.0.69
    Authors: David Tolnay
    License: MIT OR Apache-2.0
    https://github.com/dtolnay/thiserror
    Use: Ergonomic error type derivation for MorphlexError.

